PROJECT CONTEXT

Build the frontend for TrendDrop, a trend-based reservation e-commerce platform for Qatar. It connects to an existing Spring Boot backend (JWT auth, role-based access: ADMIN, TRENDS_RESPONSIBLE, CUSTOMER) exposing REST endpoints plus a WebSocket channel for real-time order notifications.

Three experiences in one app:


Public storefront — customers browse trending products and reserve them, no login required.
Trends Responsible dashboard — manage trend research, create/edit products, view stock, view own orders.
Admin dashboard — full access: user management, product approval, stock, orders, audit log, live order notifications.


Build with Next.js 14+ (App Router), TypeScript, Tailwind CSS. Code must be clean, fast-loading (this app runs paid social ad traffic to its product pages — page speed directly affects conversion), and properly typed end to end.


TECH STACK & DEPENDENCIES


next (App Router, TypeScript)
tailwindcss + shadcn/ui (component primitives — Button, Input, Dialog, Table, Badge, Toast)
@tanstack/react-query — all server data fetching/caching, not raw useEffect fetches
zustand — lightweight client state (auth user, JWT token)
axios — API client, with interceptors for JWT attach + refresh-token retry on 401
zod + react-hook-form — form validation (the "Buy Now" popup, login forms, product creation wizard)
@stomp/stompjs + sockjs-client — WebSocket client for real-time order notifications (matches backend's Spring STOMP setup)
react-i18next (or Next's built-in i18n routing) — Arabic + English, RTL support
lucide-react — icons
recharts — Admin dashboard charts (revenue, conversion)
sonner — toast notifications (used for the live "new order" popup)



