KEY PAGES — DETAILED REQUIREMENTS

1. Product Landing Page (/product/[slug]) — the most important page in the app


Use ISR (export const revalidate = 60) — page is cached and served fast to ad traffic, not rebuilt on every request.
Sections: hero media (image/video carousel — build the component so it can be swapped for a 3D viewer later without restructuring the page), variant/color selector, price, urgency counter, countdown timer if launchEnd is set, "Buy Now" button.
Buy Now opens BuyNowDialog: form fields (first name, last name, phone, email, delivery location), payment method selector (Card / Apple Pay / Google Pay / COD), validated with zod + react-hook-form.
On submit: call POST /api/orders. If payment method is CARD/APPLE_PAY/GOOGLE_PAY, redirect the user to the checkout URL returned by the backend. If COD, show a confirmation screen immediately with the tracking link.
Install the ad platform pixels (Meta Pixel, TikTok Pixel, Snap Pixel) on this page, firing a "conversion" event on successful order creation.


2. Order Tracking (/track/[orderId])


Public, no login. Shows order status timeline: Reserved → Confirmed → Processing → Out for Delivery → Delivered.
Fetch via GET /api/orders/track/{trackingId}.


3. Admin/Trends Dashboards


Protected via middleware.ts checking JWT role claim — redirect to /login if missing/wrong role.
NotificationBell: connects to the backend WebSocket (/ws, subscribe /topic/orders) on mount. On a new order event, show a toast (sonner) with product name + delivery location, and increment an unread badge. This must feel instant — no polling, pure WebSocket push.
StockTable: paginated, shows product/variant/stock qty/status, inline "Adjust" action (Admin + Trends Responsible only — this page must not exist anywhere in the (public) route group).
Product creation wizard (Trends Responsible): multi-step form — Info → Variants → Pricing → Media upload → (optional) Campaign linking. Submits as PENDING_APPROVAL.



API CLIENT PATTERN (apply consistently)

typescript// lib/api/client.ts
// - baseURL from process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL
// - request interceptor: attach Authorization: Bearer <token> from authStore
// - response interceptor: on 401, attempt refresh token once, retry original request; on refresh failure, logout + redirect /login

All API functions return typed responses matching backend's ApiResponse<T> wrapper — unwrap .data in the API layer so components never deal with the wrapper directly. Use React Query for every GET (with sensible staleTime) and mutations (useMutation) for every POST/PUT with optimistic UI where it makes sense (e.g. stock adjustment).


WEBSOCKET CLIENT SETUP

typescript// lib/websocket.ts
// Connect using @stomp/stompjs + sockjs-client to `${NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL}/ws`
// On connect: subscribe to `/topic/orders`
// On message: parse JSON payload {orderId, productName, variant, deliveryLocation, customerName, customerPhone}
// Expose a simple hook: useOrderNotifications() returning the latest notifications array + connection status
// Only initialize this connection inside admin/trends layouts — never in the public routes


ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES (.env.local)

NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8080
NEXT_PUBLIC_WS_URL=http://localhost:8080/ws
NEXT_PUBLIC_META_PIXEL_ID=
NEXT_PUBLIC_TIKTOK_PIXEL_ID=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SNAP_PIXEL_ID=


PERFORMANCE REQUIREMENTS


Product landing pages: ISR, optimized images (next/image), no client-side waterfall fetches for above-the-fold content.
Fonts: use next/font (self-hosted, no external font request blocking render).
Split dashboard code from public code — the public bundle should not include Recharts, the WebSocket client, or dashboard-only components.
Lighthouse mobile performance target: 90+ on the product landing page.



ADDITIONAL RULES FOR CURSOR


Every API call goes through lib/api/* — no fetch/axios calls directly inside components.
Every form uses react-hook-form + zod schema validation, matching backend validation rules exactly (e.g. phone format).
TypeScript strict mode on — no any types for API responses; define interfaces in lib/types matching backend DTOs.
Public routes must never import or reference stock/admin/trends components, even indirectly — keep the bundle boundary clean.
All currency displayed as QAR, formatted consistently via formatters.ts.
Arabic/English: wrap the app in an i18n provider from the start, even if only English content is written first — retrofitting RTL later is painful, building it in now is cheap.